# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values:

```bash
# GitHub Authentication (optional - can use 'contriflow auth' instead)
GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_personal_access_token_here

# OpenRouter API Key (for AI-powered suggestions)
# Get free at: https://openrouter.ai
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your_openrouter_api_key_here
```

## How to Get These Tokens

### GitHub Personal Access Token

1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
3. Select these scopes:
   - `repo` - Full control of private repositories
   - `public_repo` - Access public repositories
   - `user` - Read user profile data
4. Copy the token and paste into `.env`

### OpenRouter API Key

1. Go to https://openrouter.ai
2. Sign up (free tier available)
3. Go to your API keys dashboard
4. Copy the API key and paste into `.env`

## Security Notes

⚠️ **NEVER commit `.env` to version control!**

- Add `.env` to your `.gitignore`
- Keep tokens private
- Rotate tokens periodically
- Use different tokens for different machines if possible
